objects.name: speccom
objects.description: SpecCom is a malicious 32-bit Windows executable malware family that uses HTTP for command and control. It relies on basic XOR obfuscation and Base64-encoding to conceal communications and configurations, embedding commands within HTML comment tags. Its main capabilities include the remote execution of Windows command prompt instructions and uploading user data. SpecCom samples are generally low in sophistication, featuring no self-installing persistence and using hard-coded keys and URL paths, making detection feasible. The malware is easily signatured in network traffic due to its use of fixed arguments and indicators.

objects.name: SpecCom_get_mac_address
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern:
rule SpecCom_get_mac_address {
    meta:
        author = "NCSC"
        description = "Detects SpecCom obtaining MAC address"

    strings:
        $ = {8D 8D F0 80 FF FF 51 8D 8D FC 80 FF FF 51 C7 85 F0 80 FF FF
90 7E 00 00 FF D0 8B C8 33 C0 C6 45 F4 00 8D 7D F5 AB 66 AB AA 85 C9 0F
85 1D 01 00 00 53 6A 25 5E 6A 30 5A 6A 32 59 8B C6 66 89 45 8C 8B C2 66
89 45 8E 6A 58 8B C1 66 89 45 90}
        $ = {8D 8D 00 81 FF FF 51 8D 95 04 81 FF FF 52 C7 85 00 81 FF FF
90 7E 00 00 FF D0 85 C0 0F 85 C7 00 00 00 8B 85 9C 82 FF FF 8B C8 C1 E9
08 0F B6 D1 52 0F B6 C0 50 8B 85 98 82 FF FF 8B C8 C1 E9 18 51 8B D0 C1
EA 10 0F B6 CA 51 8B D0 C1 EA 08 0F B6 CA 0F B6 D0 51 52 8D 45 94}
    condition:
        (uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and uint16(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x4550) and any
of them
}
